# Image Steganography Application in C

## ğŸ“Œ Project Description
This project implements **Image Steganography** using the C programming language.
It hides secret text data inside a BMP image file using **bitwise manipulation**
and later retrieves the hidden data without affecting the visual appearance of the image.

---

## ğŸ›  Technologies Used
- C Programming
- File Handling
- Bitwise Operations
- Structures & Pointers
- BMP Image Format

---

## ğŸ“‚ Project Files
- encode.c / encode.h â†’ Encoding logic
- decode.c / decode.h â†’ Decoding logic
- main.c â†’ Main driver program
- common.h, types.h â†’ Common definitions
- secret.txt â†’ Input secret message
- output.txt â†’ Decoded output
- sample.bmp â†’ Source image

---

## ğŸ” Encoding Process
1. Read the source BMP image file
2. Read the secret text from `secret.txt`
3. Hide the secret data into the image using LSB (Least Significant Bit)
4. Generate a new encoded image file

---

## ğŸ”“ Decoding Process
1. Read the encoded BMP image
2. Extract hidden bits from the image
3. Reconstruct the original secret message
4. Store the decoded data in `output.txt`

---

